message.content: cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV. The paper discusses neural architectures for reading comprehension, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of linguistics features, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The experiments conducted in the paper involve analyzing hidden state vectors, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of neural readers, which is a topic in neural networks and falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of cloze-style datasets, which is a common technique in natural language processing and falls under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
